---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="mono-poly - how it works"
  description="How to move files with their commit history between git repos."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>How it works</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      How to move files with their commit history between git repos.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <p>
      Monopoly takes the commit history of the files you're moving and asks
      git to graft it into the target repo's history, alongside the files
      themselves.
    </p>

    <figure class="diagram">
      <div class="frame">
        <svg
          viewBox="0 0 720 240"
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          role="img"
          aria-label="Three boxes left to right: source repo, temp clone with filtered history, target repo. Arrows between them labeled clone plus filter-repo, and merge."
        >
          <style>
            .box {
              fill: var(--bg);
              stroke: var(--border);
              stroke-width: 1;
            }
            .h {
              font:
                600 10px ui-monospace,
                Menlo,
                monospace;
              fill: var(--fg-muted);
              letter-spacing: 0.08em;
            }
            .t {
              font:
                11px ui-monospace,
                Menlo,
                monospace;
              fill: var(--fg);
            }
            .t-mut {
              fill: var(--fg-muted);
            }
            .t-hi {
              fill: var(--highlight);
              font-weight: 600;
            }
            .arr {
              stroke: var(--accent);
              stroke-width: 1.5;
              fill: none;
            }
            .arr-h {
              fill: var(--accent);
            }
            .a-lbl {
              font:
                10px ui-monospace,
                Menlo,
                monospace;
              fill: var(--accent);
            }
            .a-sub {
              font:
                10px ui-monospace,
                Menlo,
                monospace;
              fill: var(--fg-muted);
            }
            .step {
              font:
                600 11px ui-monospace,
                Menlo,
                monospace;
              fill: var(--prompt);
            }
          </style>

          <!-- Box 1: SOURCE -->
          <rect class="box" x="0" y="50" width="200" height="170" rx="6"></rect>
          <text class="h" x="14" y="72">SOURCE REPO</text>
          <text class="t" x="14" y="98">.</text>
          <text class="t" x="14" y="114">├── apps/</text>
          <text class="t" x="14" y="130">├── packages/</text>
          <text class="t t-hi" x="14" y="146">│ └── auth/ ←</text>
          <text class="t" x="14" y="162">├── tools/</text>
          <text class="t" x="14" y="178">└── README.md</text>

          <!-- Arrow 1 -->
          <text class="step" x="230" y="98" text-anchor="middle">1</text>
          <line class="arr" x1="205" y1="135" x2="252" y2="135"></line>
          <polygon class="arr-h" points="260,135 250,131 250,139"></polygon>
          <text class="a-lbl" x="230" y="124" text-anchor="middle">clone</text>
          <text class="a-sub" x="230" y="153" text-anchor="middle"
            >+ filter-repo</text
          >

          <!-- Box 2: TEMP CLONE -->
          <rect class="box" x="260" y="50" width="200" height="170" rx="6"
          ></rect>
          <text class="h" x="274" y="72">TEMP CLONE (filtered)</text>
          <text class="t" x="274" y="98">.</text>
          <text class="t t-hi" x="274" y="114">├── login.ts</text>
          <text class="t t-hi" x="274" y="130">├── session.ts</text>
          <text class="t t-hi" x="274" y="146">└── README.md</text>
          <text class="t t-mut" x="274" y="174" font-style="italic"
            >history: only commits</text
          >
          <text class="t t-mut" x="274" y="190" font-style="italic"
            >touching packages/auth</text
          >

          <!-- Arrow 2 -->
          <text class="step" x="490" y="98" text-anchor="middle">2</text>
          <line class="arr" x1="465" y1="135" x2="512" y2="135"></line>
          <polygon class="arr-h" points="520,135 510,131 510,139"></polygon>
          <text class="a-lbl" x="490" y="124" text-anchor="middle">merge</text>
          <text class="a-sub" x="490" y="153" text-anchor="middle"
            >(unrelated)</text
          >

          <!-- Box 3: TARGET -->
          <rect class="box" x="520" y="50" width="200" height="170" rx="6"
          ></rect>
          <text class="h" x="534" y="72">TARGET REPO</text>
          <text class="t" x="534" y="98">.</text>
          <text class="t" x="534" y="114">├── existing/</text>
          <text class="t" x="534" y="130">├── README.md</text>
          <text class="t t-hi" x="534" y="150">└── auth/ + NEW</text>
          <text class="t" x="534" y="166"> ├── login.ts</text>
          <text class="t" x="534" y="182"> ├── session.ts</text>
          <text class="t" x="534" y="198"> └── README.md</text>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <figcaption>
        Bird's eye view of the process; all "dirty" work is done in a temporary
        repo.
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>1. Clone the source into a temp dir</h2>
    <p>
      Create a temporary clone of the source repo so the rewriting that
      follows can't affect your real repo or its history.
    </p>
    <pre><code>git clone --single-branch &lt;source&gt; &lt;tmp&gt;/extract</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>2. Filter history to just the path you care about</h2>
    <p>
      <a href="https://github.com/newren/git-filter-repo"
        ><code>git filter-repo</code></a
      > rewrites the commit graph of the temp clone, keeping only commits that
      touched the path you're moving.
    </p>
    <pre><code># for a directory:
git filter-repo --subdirectory-filter packages/auth --force

# for a single file:
git filter-repo --path src/logger.ts --force</code></pre>

    <figure class="diagram">
      <div class="frame">
        <svg
          viewBox="0 0 720 240"
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          role="img"
          aria-label="Top timeline of nine commits with four highlighted as touching the target path. Down arrow labeled git filter-repo. Bottom timeline shows just those four commits remaining."
        >
          <style>
            .ax {
              stroke: var(--border);
              stroke-width: 1;
            }
            .dot {
              fill: var(--bg);
              stroke: var(--fg-muted);
              stroke-width: 1.2;
            }
            .dot-hi {
              fill: var(--highlight);
              stroke: var(--highlight);
            }
            .lbl {
              font:
                11px ui-monospace,
                Menlo,
                monospace;
              fill: var(--fg-muted);
            }
            .lbl-strong {
              fill: var(--fg);
            }
            .lbl-hi {
              fill: var(--highlight);
              font-weight: 600;
            }
            .arr2 {
              stroke: var(--accent);
              stroke-width: 1.5;
              fill: none;
            }
            .arr2-h {
              fill: var(--accent);
            }
            .a2 {
              font:
                11px ui-monospace,
                Menlo,
                monospace;
              fill: var(--accent);
            }
            .a2-sub {
              fill: var(--fg-muted);
            }
          </style>

          <text class="lbl lbl-strong" x="10" y="30">Source history</text>
          <text class="lbl" x="120" y="30">— every commit on the branch</text>

          <line class="ax" x1="60" y1="65" x2="660" y2="65"></line>
          <circle class="dot" cx="80" cy="65" r="6"></circle>
          <circle class="dot dot-hi" cx="150" cy="65" r="6"></circle>
          <circle class="dot" cx="220" cy="65" r="6"></circle>
          <circle class="dot dot-hi" cx="290" cy="65" r="6"></circle>
          <circle class="dot" cx="360" cy="65" r="6"></circle>
          <circle class="dot" cx="430" cy="65" r="6"></circle>
          <circle class="dot dot-hi" cx="500" cy="65" r="6"></circle>
          <circle class="dot" cx="570" cy="65" r="6"></circle>
          <circle class="dot dot-hi" cx="640" cy="65" r="6"></circle>

          <text class="lbl lbl-hi" x="660" y="50" text-anchor="end">●</text>
          <text class="lbl" x="675" y="50">touched packages/auth</text>

          <line class="arr2" x1="360" y1="85" x2="360" y2="148"></line>
          <polygon class="arr2-h" points="360,156 356,146 364,146"></polygon>
          <text class="a2" x="375" y="110">git filter-repo</text>
          <text class="a2 a2-sub" x="375" y="126"
            >--subdirectory-filter packages/auth</text
          >

          <text class="lbl lbl-strong" x="10" y="195">Filtered history</text>
          <text class="lbl" x="135" y="195"
            >— path-touching commits, in order</text
          >

          <line class="ax" x1="60" y1="220" x2="660" y2="220"></line>
          <circle class="dot dot-hi" cx="120" cy="220" r="6"></circle>
          <circle class="dot dot-hi" cx="280" cy="220" r="6"></circle>
          <circle class="dot dot-hi" cx="440" cy="220" r="6"></circle>
          <circle class="dot dot-hi" cx="600" cy="220" r="6"></circle>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <figcaption>
        The four commits that touched <code>packages/auth</code> survive,
        with author, date, and message preserved.
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>3. Restructure paths to match <code>--as</code></h2>
    <p>
      If you passed <code>--as</code>, monopoly uses <code>git mv</code> to
      move the files to that path and records a chore commit.
    </p>

    <figure class="diagram">
      <div class="frame">
        <svg
          viewBox="0 0 720 200"
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          role="img"
          aria-label="Two boxes: left shows files at the repo root after subdirectory-filter; right shows the same files moved under the target as path."
        >
          <style>
            .box3 {
              fill: var(--bg);
              stroke: var(--border);
              stroke-width: 1;
            }
            .h3 {
              font:
                600 10px ui-monospace,
                Menlo,
                monospace;
              fill: var(--fg-muted);
              letter-spacing: 0.06em;
            }
            .t3 {
              font:
                11px ui-monospace,
                Menlo,
                monospace;
              fill: var(--fg);
            }
            .t3-mut {
              fill: var(--fg-muted);
            }
            .t3-hi {
              fill: var(--highlight);
            }
            .arr3 {
              stroke: var(--accent);
              stroke-width: 1.5;
              fill: none;
            }
            .arr3-h {
              fill: var(--accent);
            }
            .a3 {
              font:
                10px ui-monospace,
                Menlo,
                monospace;
              fill: var(--accent);
            }
            .a3-sub {
              font:
                10px ui-monospace,
                Menlo,
                monospace;
              fill: var(--fg-muted);
            }
          </style>

          <rect class="box3" x="10" y="20" width="290" height="160" rx="6"
          ></rect>
          <text class="h3" x="24" y="42">AFTER FILTER</text>
          <text class="t3" x="24" y="68">.</text>
          <text class="t3 t3-hi" x="24" y="86">├── login.ts</text>
          <text class="t3 t3-hi" x="24" y="104">├── session.ts</text>
          <text class="t3 t3-hi" x="24" y="122">└── README.md</text>
          <text class="t3 t3-mut" x="24" y="150" font-style="italic"
            >files at repo root</text
          >
          <text class="t3 t3-mut" x="24" y="166" font-style="italic"
            >(prefix stripped)</text
          >

          <line class="arr3" x1="305" y1="100" x2="412" y2="100"></line>
          <polygon class="arr3-h" points="420,100 410,96 410,104"></polygon>
          <text class="a3" x="360" y="90" text-anchor="middle">git mv</text>
          <text class="a3-sub" x="360" y="118" text-anchor="middle"
            >+ chore commit</text
          >

          <rect class="box3" x="425" y="20" width="290" height="160" rx="6"
          ></rect>
          <text class="h3" x="439" y="42">AFTER RESTRUCTURE (--as auth)</text>
          <text class="t3" x="439" y="68">.</text>
          <text class="t3" x="439" y="86">└── auth/</text>
          <text class="t3 t3-hi" x="439" y="104"> ├── login.ts</text>
          <text class="t3 t3-hi" x="439" y="122"> ├── session.ts</text>
          <text class="t3 t3-hi" x="439" y="140"> └── README.md</text>
          <text class="t3 t3-mut" x="439" y="166" font-style="italic"
            >ready for merge</text
          >
        </svg>
      </div>
      <figcaption>
        Captured as a <code>chore(monopoly): restructure for target path</code>
        commit.
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>4. Merge into the target repo</h2>
    <p>
      Source and target repos share no commits, so the merge needs
      <code>--allow-unrelated-histories</code>.
    </p>
    <pre><code>cd &lt;target&gt;
git remote add monopoly-temp &lt;tmp&gt;/extract    # local path, no network
git fetch monopoly-temp                       # pull the filtered history in
git merge monopoly-temp/&lt;branch&gt; \
  --allow-unrelated-histories \               # override: no common ancestor
  --no-commit                                 # stage the merge, don't commit
git remote remove monopoly-temp               # cleanup</code></pre>
    <p>
      The filtered commits attach as a parallel ancestry meeting at the merge
      commit, so <code>git log --follow</code> and <code>git blame</code> walk straight
      back to the originals.
    </p>
  </section>
<section>
    <h2>5. Hand the merge off to you</h2>
    <p>
      The merge stops at <code>--no-commit</code>. monopoly writes a
      descriptive message into <code>.git/MERGE_MSG</code> (source repo,
      source path, source HEAD, commit count) and steps out. You run <code>git commit</code> when you're happy.
    </p>
    <p>
      This gives you time to evaluate changes and do follow-up work in target (fixing build, adding docs, etc.)
    </p>
  </section>
  <section>
    <h2>6. Optional: one continuous history</h2>
    <p>
      Once you commit, <code>git log --follow</code> and <code>git blame</code>
      already walk across the move. The one thing they don't do is collapse the
      two starting commits into a single line — so plain <code>git log</code>,
      <code>git bisect</code>, and stacked relay moves still see a fork.
    </p>
    <p>
      To fix that, monopoly prints a ready-to-run
      <code>git replace --graft</code> command after each move, with the
      imported root and target tip already filled in:
    </p>
    <pre><code>git replace --graft &lt;imported-root&gt; &lt;target-tip&gt;   # re-parent, no rewrite
git push origin 'refs/replace/*'                    # share it with the team
git config --add remote.origin.fetch '+refs/replace/*:refs/replace/*'</code></pre>
    <p>
      A graft is an overlay ref, not a history rewrite: it never touches a
      commit object. Delete it (<code>git replace -d</code>) and you're back to
      the plain, still fully reachable, history. Replace refs don't travel with
      a normal clone, which is why sharing needs the explicit push and fetch
      config above.
    </p>
  </section>
  <section>
    <h2>About <code>--allow-unrelated-histories</code></h2>

    <h3>What it means</h3>
    <p>
      A merge needs a single commit that the two branches last shared. In
      monopoly's case we have two repos that were never connected, so there
      isn't one. The flag tells git "merge them anyway." The result has two
      starting commits in its history.
    </p>

    <h3>The risk</h3>
    <p>
      If you move a file to a path that already exists in the target repo,
      the two versions share no past. Git can't pick a winner, so the merge
      produces a conflict you need to resolve manually.
    </p>

    <h3>Safety nets</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>
        When conflicts happen, <strong>monopoly auto-aborts</strong> and asks
        you to pick a different <code>--as</code>.
      </li>
      <li>
        Resetting the target repo is one command:
        <code>git merge --abort</code>.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Monopoly always uses <code>--no-commit</code>.</strong> You
        run the final commit step.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3>What you still have to mind</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Type the right <code>&lt;source&gt;</code> and <code>--to</code>.</strong>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Target must be on the branch you want the files to land on.</strong>
        Whatever's checked out in the target is what gets the merge.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Read the diff before <code>git commit</code>.</strong>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Try <code>--dry-run</code> first</strong> to validate paths.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="squash-merges">About squash-merges</h2>

    <h3>What squash does</h3>
    <p>
      A squash-merge takes the diff a merge would introduce and writes it
      as one new commit on top of the target branch. The merge commit and
      its imported parents are not part of the new commit's ancestry.
    </p>

    <h3>What this does to monopoly's work</h3>
    <p>
      Monopoly's whole value sits in the parallel ancestry the merge
      commit creates — that's the chain <code>git log --follow</code> and
      <code>git blame</code> walk back through to find the originals.
      Squash flattens that ancestry. After the squash:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <code>git log --follow</code> on the moved file shows one commit,
        by whoever ran the squash, dated "now".
      </li>
      <li>
        <code>git blame</code> attributes every line to that same squash
        commit. Original authorship is gone from the target repo.
      </li>
      <li>
        The filter-repo'd commits still exist as unreachable objects
        until <code>git gc</code> drops them, but nothing in the visible
        history points at them anymore.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3>The recommendation</h3>
    <p>
      <strong>Don't squash a monopoly PR.</strong> Use a regular merge
      commit. If your repo defaults to squash-merge, switch to "Create a
      merge commit" on that one PR (GitHub's merge button has a dropdown).
    </p>

    <h3>If a squash already happened</h3>
    <p>
      The original commits still live in the source repo — you can
      <code>git log</code> there for archaeology. Blame in the target
      repo will lie, but the past isn't actually destroyed, just hidden.
    </p>
  </section>


</BaseLayout>